# SmartPark - Smart Parking Management System

A full-stack React application with Node.js backend for smart parking management with admin and user portals.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend["Frontend (React + Vite)"]
        A[Auth Pages] --> B[Admin Dashboard]
        A --> C[User Dashboard]
        B --> D[Parking Management]
        B --> E[CCTV & Slot Drawing]
        B --> F[Booking History]
        B --> G[Slot Release]
        C --> H[Parking Discovery]
        C --> I[Slot Selection & Booking]
        C --> J[Razorpay Payment]
        C --> K[Navigation]
        C --> L[Ticket View]
    end
    
    subgraph Backend["Backend (Node.js + Express)"]
        M[Auth API] --> N[JWT Middleware]
        O[Parking API]
        P[Booking API]
        Q[Payment API - Razorpay]
        R[Slot Detection API]
    end
    
    subgraph Database["MongoDB Atlas"]
        S[Users Collection]
        T[ParkingAreas Collection]
        U[Slots Collection]
        V[Bookings Collection]
    end
    
    Frontend --> Backend --> Database
```

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Razorpay & MongoDB Credentials**: The provided credentials will be stored in a `.env` file in the backend. Never commit this file to version control.

> [!WARNING]
> **CCTV Slot Detection**: Real-time object detection on CCTV feeds typically requires a Python/ML backend (e.g., YOLO, OpenCV). For this implementation, we will:
> - Allow admins to draw slot coordinates on a CCTV frame/image
> - Simulate occupancy detection with manual toggle + visual overlay
> - The CCTV URL will render as a video/image feed with drawn slot boundaries
> - Admins can manually mark slots as occupied/empty, or a future ML service can be integrated

> [!NOTE]
> **MongoDB Atlas Connection**: We'll construct the connection string using the provided credentials. Ensure the MongoDB Atlas cluster has network access enabled (0.0.0.0/0 for development).

